race.comment: TAVROS (3) stretches out to the 2000m for the first time and this looks a target race. Snagged back early and like the way he attacked the line when fifth to Osipenko over 1600m in the Little Dance at Randwick. Key jockey change and the awkward draw is no real concern. Leading player. BLACKLIST (7) ticking over nicely for this and can figure prominently with the 55.5kg. Struck trouble in the run when fifth over 1900m at Canterbury at BM72 grade. Maps well and can take a hand in the finish. DEEL ME A QUEEN (20) Dundeel mare who drops sharply in weight on the limit. Arrives here deep into the prep after surging late with the 60kg when third over 2200m at Scone. Gets cover early and represents great value. POISEN POINT (8) holding her form at Highway level and winning rider hops back aboard. Keep safe. BEHTAR (17) capable on his day and assess on his narrow fourth over 1800m here two-back. Down in the weights and goes into the exotics.
